violet /ˈvaɪəlɪt/

(violets) 

1. N-COUNT A violet is a small plant that has purple or white flowers in the spring. 紫罗兰 

2. COLOR Something that is violet is a bluish-purple colour. 紫罗兰色的 

例： The light was beginning to drain from a violet sky. 光线正开始从紫罗兰色的天空中渐渐消失。 

3. PHRASE If you say that someone is no shrinking violet , you mean that they are not at all shy. 羞涩的人 

例： When it comes to expressing himself he is no shrinking violet. 他表达自己看法时一点都不羞涩。

